  m_text: Potatoes are starchy root vegetables that grow underground as tubers on
    the roots of the potato plant. They typically have a round to oval shape with
    thin skin that can be brown, yellow, red, or even purple, and a flesh that ranges
    from white to golden in color. Potatoes are rich in carbohydrates, making them
    an excellent source of energy, and they also provide nutrients such as vitamin
    C, potassium, and fiber. They thrive in cool climates and well-drained soil,
    where the tubers develop beneath the surface while leafy green stems grow above
    ground. Potatoes are one of the most versatile foods in the world and can be
    prepared in countless ways, including baking, boiling, frying, and mashing.
