  m_text: Lemon trees are small to medium-sized evergreen trees known for their glossy
    green leaves, fragrant white blossoms, and bright yellow citrus fruits. They
    typically grow in warm, sunny climates and can reach heights of 10 to 20 feet,
    though they can also be kept smaller when cultivated in pots. The flowers of
    a lemon tree are highly aromatic, often filling the air with a sweet scent before
    developing into lemons with a thick rind and juicy, acidic pulp. Lemon trees
    require well-drained soil, regular watering, and plenty of sunlight to thrive.
    In addition to their culinary uses in beverages, cooking, and baking, lemon trees
    are also valued for their ornamental beauty and refreshing fragrance.
