  m_text: "Plum trees are deciduous fruit trees known for their attractive blossoms
    and sweet, juicy fruits. They typically grow to heights of 10 to 25 feet and
    produce clusters of delicate white or pale pink flowers in early spring before
    their leaves fully emerge. The fruit that follows can vary in color\u2014ranging
    from deep purple and red to yellow\u2014depending on the variety, and has smooth
    skin with a soft, flavorful flesh surrounding a single hard pit. Plum trees thrive
    in temperate climates with well-drained soil and plenty of sunlight. In addition
    to providing fresh fruit, plums are commonly used in jams, desserts, and juices,
    making these trees both ornamental and highly practical in gardens and orchards."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
